Which statement is true about the DriverManager class?

A.It returns an instance of Connection.
B.it executes SQL statements against the database.
C.It only queries metadata of the database.
D.it is written by different vendors for their specific database.

Explanation and Answer:
Option A, using getConnection method of the DriverManager class, can connect to the repository and get the Connection object entity. This is the correct answer.

Option B, Statement object can execute SQL statement.

Option C, DriverManager is used to load JDBC Driver and connection database.

Option D, this description describes the Driver category.